edu.mines.jtk.util

Interface Float4


  • public interface Float4
    A generic interface for a 4-D array of floats. This interface enables getting and setting 1-, 2-, 3- and 4-D subarrays (slices) of elements from any data structure that can be indexed like a 4-D array. Unlike a 4-D array, that data structure need not reside entirely in memory.

    Logically, the 4-D array can be considered as float a[n4][n3][n2][n1], where n1 is the fastest array dimension, and n4 is the slowest.

    Version:
    2012.05.28
    Author:
    Dave Hale, Colorado School of Mines

           int j3,
           int j4,
           float[] s)
        Gets the specified subarray of elements into the specified 1-D array. The length of the array must be at least m1*m2*m3*m4.
        Parameters:
        m1 - number of elements in 1st dimension of subarray.
        m2 - number of elements in 2nd dimension of subarray.
        m3 - number of elements in 3rd dimension of subarray.
        m4 - number of elements in 4th dimension of subarray.
        j1 - index of first element in 1st dimension of subarray.
        j2 - index of first element in 2nd dimension of subarray.
        j3 - index of first element in 3rd dimension of subarray.
        j4 - index of first element in 4th dimension of subarray.
        s - array[m1*m2*m3*m4] of elements of the specified subarray.
